3.2.2. Biogeography.
Cannabis, one of the most common
drugs on the illicit market, is grown all over the world
and increasingly in local production in European countries,
the United States, and Canada. Its resin form (hashish)
is produced in about 60 countries and its main sources
are North Africa and the countries of Southwest Asia
